## ğŸ›  Features

- âœ… Manage **Products**, **Suppliers**, **Warehouses**, and **Stock**
- âœ… Monitor inventory levels
- âœ… Get alerts when stock goes below threshold
- âœ… Perform stock transfer between warehouses
- âœ… Automate alerts using **SQL triggers**
- âœ… Use stored procedures to execute complex logic

## ğŸ—ƒ Database Schema

### `Products`
| Column      | Type          |
|-------------|---------------|
| ProductID   | INT (PK)      |
| ProductName | VARCHAR(100)  |
| Price       | DECIMAL(10,2) |

### `Suppliers`
| Column       | Type          |
|--------------|---------------|
| SupplierID   | INT (PK)      |
| SupplierName | VARCHAR(100)  |
| ContactInfo  | VARCHAR(100)  |

### `Warehouses`
| Column      | Type          |
|-------------|---------------|
| WarehouseID | INT (PK)      |
| Location    | VARCHAR(100)  |

### `Stock`
| Column      | Type          |
|-------------|---------------|
| StockID     | INT (PK)      |
| ProductID   | INT (FK)      |
| WarehouseID | INT (FK)      |
| Quantity    | INT           |

### `LowStockLog` (for alerts)
| Column     | Type      |
|------------|-----------|
| LogID      | INT (PK)  |
| ProductID  | INT       |
| Quantity   | INT       |
| AlertTime  | TIMESTAMP |

